Text.SourceString: Whoa, are you the one everyone's been bubbling about? The ocean cleaner that even the king mentions?
Text.LocalizedString: Whoa, are you the one everyone's been bubbling about? The ocean cleaner that even the king mentions?

Text.SourceString: Welcome to the Kingdom! I'm <NPCName>Jannu</>, proud owner of the Sleepy Eel Tavern.//Never thought I'd see the day when a land-dweller would make waves like this around here.
Text.LocalizedString: Welcome to the Kingdom! I'm <NPCName>Jannu</>, proud owner of the Sleepy Eel Tavern.//Never thought I'd see the day when a land-dweller would make waves like this around here.

Text.SourceString: Huh? Never mind, then.//I'm <NPCName>Jannu</>, proud owner of the Sleepy Eel Tavern.
Text.LocalizedString: Huh? Never mind, then.//I'm <NPCName>Jannu</>, proud owner of the Sleepy Eel Tavern.

Special.SourceString: I don't know what you're talking about.
Special.LocalizedString: I don't know what you're talking about.

Text.SourceString: I'm <NPCName>Jannu</>, proud owner of the Sleepy Eel Tavern. Never thought I'd see the day when a land-dweller would make waves like this around here.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm <NPCName>Jannu</>, proud owner of the Sleepy Eel Tavern. Never thought I'd see the day when a land-dweller would make waves like this around here.

Text.SourceString: You feel that rhythm? That's the rain dancing up top. Brings a whole different vibe down here – kind of soothing.
Text.LocalizedString: You feel that rhythm? That's the rain dancing up top. Brings a whole different vibe down here – kind of soothing.

Text.SourceString: Love the rain, I do. Perfect excuse to whip up some special drinks and enjoy the mellow tunes.
Text.LocalizedString: Love the rain, I do. Perfect excuse to whip up some special drinks and enjoy the mellow tunes.

Text.SourceString: If I break into song, promise you won't swim off, alright? Haha!
Text.LocalizedString: If I break into song, promise you won't swim off, alright? Haha!

Text.SourceString: Rain's got a way of softening the whole sea.
Text.LocalizedString: Rain's got a way of softening the whole sea.

Text.SourceString: Whoa, these storms really churn the waters! How is it up there, on the land?
Text.LocalizedString: Whoa, these storms really churn the waters! How is it up there, on the land?

Text.SourceString: Snow's something else, isn't it?
Text.LocalizedString: Snow's something else, isn't it?

Text.SourceString: Snow falling through the water is a sight to see – kinda magical.//It's days like these I miss my singing days, but hey, the Eel's warm and toasty, ready for ya!
Text.LocalizedString: Snow falling through the water is a sight to see – kinda magical.//It's days like these I miss my singing days, but hey, the Eel's warm and toasty, ready for ya!

Text.SourceString: Ah, Winter's chill in the sea – it's brisk, but invigorating. You see the fish moving a bit slower, more gracefully.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, Winter's chill in the sea – it's brisk, but invigorating. You see the fish moving a bit slower, more gracefully.

Text.SourceString: Land farmers like you must have it tough in the Winter, with all that frost.
Text.LocalizedString: Land farmers like you must have it tough in the Winter, with all that frost.

Text.SourceString: You're finding yourself with free time now, aren't you?//What do you do, just sleep through until the sun decides to show up again or?
Text.LocalizedString: You're finding yourself with free time now, aren't you?//What do you do, just sleep through until the sun decides to show up again or?

Text.SourceString: You should see the coral blooms in my garden right now – they're bursting with colors.
Text.LocalizedString: You should see the coral blooms in my garden right now – they're bursting with colors.

Text.SourceString: You should see the coral blooms in my garden right now – they're bursting with colors.
Text.LocalizedString: You should see the coral blooms in my garden right now – they're bursting with colors.

Text.SourceString: There's this one fish, I've named him Nibbler. He's got a knack for nibbling on the plants in my garden.//I try to shoo him away, but I think he sees it as a game. He's winning, by the way.
Text.LocalizedString: There's this one fish, I've named him Nibbler. He's got a knack for nibbling on the plants in my garden.//I try to shoo him away, but I think he sees it as a game. He's winning, by the way.

Text.SourceString: And then there's this one pesky sea snail, I call him Muncher. Don't get me started.
Text.LocalizedString: And then there's this one pesky sea snail, I call him Muncher. Don't get me started.

Text.SourceString: Olan's a whiz in the kitchen, sure, but let's be real – it's all about the ingredients, right? I mean, a chef is only as good as what he's got in his pantry.
Text.LocalizedString: Olan's a whiz in the kitchen, sure, but let's be real – it's all about the ingredients, right? I mean, a chef is only as good as what he's got in his pantry.

Text.SourceString: And as for a garden, well, the kingdom's got one, but it's a swim away in the next ocean. We're talking about what we have right here in our own waters.
Text.LocalizedString: And as for a garden, well, the kingdom's got one, but it's a swim away in the next ocean. We're talking about what we have right here in our own waters.

Text.SourceString: Can I get you something to drink?
Text.LocalizedString: Can I get you something to drink?

Text.SourceString: Ready to order?
Text.LocalizedString: Ready to order?

Text.SourceString: You have to try my creation, the 'Oceanic Mojito.'//It's got a bit of everything: glowing algae, some pearl dust, and just a splash of deep-sea nectar. Took me ages to get it just right, but I think it's a winner.
Text.LocalizedString: You have to try my creation, the 'Oceanic Mojito.'//It's got a bit of everything: glowing algae, some pearl dust, and just a splash of deep-sea nectar. Took me ages to get it just right, but I think it's a winner.

Text.SourceString: You land-dwellers really know how to throw a party! Last time I popped up, it was right in the middle of a huge festival – lights in the sky, music floating over the waves.//I hung around just long enough to dance to a few tunes with my partner.
Text.LocalizedString: You land-dwellers really know how to throw a party! Last time I popped up, it was right in the middle of a huge festival – lights in the sky, music floating over the waves.//I hung around just long enough to dance to a few tunes with my partner.

Text.SourceString: We're not together anymore. It's for the best.
Text.LocalizedString: We're not together anymore. It's for the best.

Text.SourceString: It's been ages since I've spent more than a few hours on the surface.
Text.LocalizedString: It's been ages since I've spent more than a few hours on the surface.

Text.SourceString: Once, I ended up at the surface during a rainstorm. Spotted this boat, right in the middle of nowhere. Just two folks on it, looked pretty frightened. I kept a watch from a distance – wasn't about to let anything bad happen to them.
Text.LocalizedString: Once, I ended up at the surface during a rainstorm. Spotted this boat, right in the middle of nowhere. Just two folks on it, looked pretty frightened. I kept a watch from a distance – wasn't about to let anything bad happen to them.

Text.SourceString: That boat, bright red it was, hard to miss.
Text.LocalizedString: That boat, bright red it was, hard to miss.

Text.SourceString: I've got this special blend of soil right outside my grotto, mixed with crushed corn and seaweed compost.//It works wonders for my sea lettuce – grows twice as lush as the regular stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: I've got this special blend of soil right outside my grotto, mixed with crushed corn and seaweed compost.//It works wonders for my sea lettuce – grows twice as lush as the regular stuff.

Text.SourceString: You wouldn't believe the difference a bit of volcanic ash makes in my garden. I gather it from the nearby undersea vents.
Text.LocalizedString: You wouldn't believe the difference a bit of volcanic ash makes in my garden. I gather it from the nearby undersea vents.

Text.SourceString: It's a bit of a swim, but my anemone blooms are the envy of the reef because of it.
Text.LocalizedString: It's a bit of a swim, but my anemone blooms are the envy of the reef because of it.

Text.SourceString: I've been experimenting with moonlight gardening. Believe it or not, certain corals respond to the lunar cycle.//My night-blooming corallines are thriving like never before.
Text.LocalizedString: I've been experimenting with moonlight gardening. Believe it or not, certain corals respond to the lunar cycle.//My night-blooming corallines are thriving like never before.

Text.SourceString: Maintaining pH levels in an underwater garden is tricky.//But hey, a sprinkle of shell powder here and there, and my kelp sprouts are happy as clams.
Text.LocalizedString: Maintaining pH levels in an underwater garden is tricky.//But hey, a sprinkle of shell powder here and there, and my kelp sprouts are happy as clams.

Text.SourceString: Set up my own little current redirect with some well-placed rocks.//It's pretty neat – gives the garden the perfect mix of nutrients and stops the leaves from getting buried under silt.
Text.LocalizedString: Set up my own little current redirect with some well-placed rocks.//It's pretty neat – gives the garden the perfect mix of nutrients and stops the leaves from getting buried under silt.

Text.SourceString: Running the Sleepy Eel isn't just about serving drinks. It's about creating a vibe.//I've decked the place out with these glowing shell lanterns – really sets a mood.
Text.LocalizedString: Running the Sleepy Eel isn't just about serving drinks. It's about creating a vibe.//I've decked the place out with these glowing shell lanterns – really sets a mood.

Text.SourceString: Every week, I dive out to collect fresh seaweed and herbs for the Eel's kitchen.//The flavors we get are unbeatable – nothing like those stale imports.
Text.LocalizedString: Every week, I dive out to collect fresh seaweed and herbs for the Eel's kitchen.//The flavors we get are unbeatable – nothing like those stale imports.

Text.SourceString: The best in the area, not even the Kingdom's kitchen has this quality. Oh yeah, I went there.
Text.LocalizedString: The best in the area, not even the Kingdom's kitchen has this quality. Oh yeah, I went there.

Text.SourceString: I like to mix it up with the regulars – they throw me a mood, and I whip up a drink to match.//It's all fun and games, and it sure keeps my mixing game on point.
Text.LocalizedString: I like to mix it up with the regulars – they throw me a mood, and I whip up a drink to match.//It's all fun and games, and it sure keeps my mixing game on point.

Text.SourceString: The Eel's got its own kind of decor. I got them myself, collected from around. Artistic, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: The Eel's got its own kind of decor. I got them myself, collected from around. Artistic, huh?

Text.SourceString: Welcome to the Sleepy Eel! Grab a seat wherever you like.
Text.LocalizedString: Welcome to the Sleepy Eel! Grab a seat wherever you like.

Text.SourceString: Ah, see those pieces over there? The giant kegs? Pulled it from a shipwreck off the Northern Reef.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, see those pieces over there? The giant kegs? Pulled it from a shipwreck off the Northern Reef.

Text.SourceString: If the walls of the Sleepy Eel could talk, oh the stories they'd tell! But since they can't, I guess I'll have to do. What are you in the mood to hear – tales of treasure, storms, or maybe something a little more mysterious?
Text.LocalizedString: If the walls of the Sleepy Eel could talk, oh the stories they'd tell! But since they can't, I guess I'll have to do. What are you in the mood to hear – tales of treasure, storms, or maybe something a little more mysterious?

Text.SourceString: Ah, treasure! Well, there's the tale of the Sunken Sapphire – a gem as big as your fist, said to be hidden in the deepest trench.//Many have searched, but it's more than just the depth that guards it... Let's just say, the sea keeps its secrets well.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, treasure! Well, there's the tale of the Sunken Sapphire – a gem as big as your fist, said to be hidden in the deepest trench.//Many have searched, but it's more than just the depth that guards it... Let's just say, the sea keeps its secrets well.

Special.SourceString: Tell me about a treasure! I love a good hunt story.
Special.LocalizedString: Tell me about a treasure! I love a good hunt story.

Text.SourceString: Storms, huh? Well, there was the Great Gale of Galeth's Ridge. Waves as tall as mountains, winds howling like sea monsters.//I was just a guppy then, but I remember the elders bracing against the storm.//We talk about the sea's beauty often, but that day, we respected its power.
Text.LocalizedString: Storms, huh? Well, there was the Great Gale of Galeth's Ridge. Waves as tall as mountains, winds howling like sea monsters.//I was just a guppy then, but I remember the elders bracing against the storm.//We talk about the sea's beauty often, but that day, we respected its power.

Special.SourceString: I'm curious about the storms. What's the wildest one you've seen?
Special.LocalizedString: I'm curious about the storms. What's the wildest one you've seen?

Text.SourceString: Something mysterious? Well, there's the Whispering Current.//Travelers speak of a place where the water hums, a melody without a source. Some say it's an ancient merfolk song lost to time, others think it's the ocean's own voice.//I've swum those waters once, and let's just say, the ocean's depths hold more secrets than we can fathom.
Text.LocalizedString: Something mysterious? Well, there's the Whispering Current.//Travelers speak of a place where the water hums, a melody without a source. Some say it's an ancient merfolk song lost to time, others think it's the ocean's own voice.//I've swum those waters once, and let's just say, the ocean's depths hold more secrets than we can fathom.

Special.SourceString: I'd like to hear something more mysterious, something unexplained.
Special.LocalizedString: I'd like to hear something more mysterious, something unexplained.

Text.SourceString: Agung once tried that frozen seaweed special we had. Ended up with his tongue stuck to it!//That guy is something else.
Text.LocalizedString: Agung once tried that frozen seaweed special we had. Ended up with his tongue stuck to it!//That guy is something else.

Text.SourceString: I overheard that one of guards tried to outswim a dolphin once. Let’s just say, it didn’t go as planned, but they had a good laugh about it.//<NPCName>Semeru</>, though, he didn’t think it was so funny – not during patrol hours.
Text.LocalizedString: I overheard that one of guards tried to outswim a dolphin once. Let’s just say, it didn’t go as planned, but they had a good laugh about it.//<NPCName>Semeru</>, though, he didn’t think it was so funny – not during patrol hours.

Text.SourceString: Oddly enough, I’ve never seen <NPCName>Agung</> and <NPCName>Denali</> hanging out here after work. Guess their patrol partnership doesn’t extend to off-duty hours.
Text.LocalizedString: Oddly enough, I’ve never seen <NPCName>Agung</> and <NPCName>Denali</> hanging out here after work. Guess their patrol partnership doesn’t extend to off-duty hours.

Text.SourceString: I always say, if I weren't doing my own thing, running the Eel, I'd probably be in the Kingdom's kitchen, cooking up a storm.//Now, I'm not saying <NPCName>Olan</>'s not good, but I reckon I'd give him a run for his money.
Text.LocalizedString: I always say, if I weren't doing my own thing, running the Eel, I'd probably be in the Kingdom's kitchen, cooking up a storm.//Now, I'm not saying <NPCName>Olan</>'s not good, but I reckon I'd give him a run for his money.

Text.SourceString: My singing days are pretty much behind me. My throat just can't handle it anymore, too many strains and things to watch out for.
Text.LocalizedString: My singing days are pretty much behind me. My throat just can't handle it anymore, too many strains and things to watch out for.

Text.SourceString: But hey, I still enjoy singing now and then, just for the fun of it – not as a career move, though.
Text.LocalizedString: But hey, I still enjoy singing now and then, just for the fun of it – not as a career move, though.

Text.SourceString: Hmm-hmm-hmm... You recognize that melody? It's a classic from the coastal reefs – always brings back good memories when I hum it.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm-hmm-hmm... You recognize that melody? It's a classic from the coastal reefs – always brings back good memories when I hum it.

Text.SourceString: Oh, the waves roll high~ and the stars shine bright, over the endless blue we roam~
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, the waves roll high~ and the stars shine bright, over the endless blue we roam~

Text.SourceString: Doo wop doo wam, we sway with the seaweed~
Text.LocalizedString: Doo wop doo wam, we sway with the seaweed~

Text.SourceString: Dubi dubidam dam, swirling like the currents~//Where the waves kiss the sky and the seagulls fly, that's where our tales are spun~
Text.LocalizedString: Dubi dubidam dam, swirling like the currents~//Where the waves kiss the sky and the seagulls fly, that's where our tales are spun~

Text.SourceString: Doo wop doo wam, under the moon's gleam~
Text.LocalizedString: Doo wop doo wam, under the moon's gleam~

Text.SourceString: La la la lum, in the heart of the brine~//Shoo bop shoo bam, where the sun doesn't shine~
Text.LocalizedString: La la la lum, in the heart of the brine~//Shoo bop shoo bam, where the sun doesn't shine~

Text.SourceString: In the heart of the sea where the spirits are free, is the place we merfolk call home~
Text.LocalizedString: In the heart of the sea where the spirits are free, is the place we merfolk call home~

Text.SourceString: Bim bam bim boom, where the coral reefs bloom~
Text.LocalizedString: Bim bam bim boom, where the coral reefs bloom~

Text.SourceString: From the depths so deep, where the ancient ones sleep, to the surface kissed by the sun~
Text.LocalizedString: From the depths so deep, where the ancient ones sleep, to the surface kissed by the sun~

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Princess Miranjani</>'s fish, Maharaja Putput, really knows how to stir things up.//Zipped right through a hoop of pearls at the royal party – everyone's still gabbing about it!
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Princess Miranjani</>'s fish, Maharaja Putput, really knows how to stir things up.//Zipped right through a hoop of pearls at the royal party – everyone's still gabbing about it!

Text.SourceString: I'll never forget the day Maharaja Putput got lost in the kelp forest. The entire palace was in a frenzy! But <NPCName>Princess Miranjani</> found him in no time.
Text.LocalizedString: I'll never forget the day Maharaja Putput got lost in the kelp forest. The entire palace was in a frenzy! But <NPCName>Princess Miranjani</> found him in no time.

Text.SourceString: Now, Nagalita, that's a different story – way more chill.//Gotta say, between you and me, I'm more of a Nagalita fan myself.
Text.LocalizedString: Now, Nagalita, that's a different story – way more chill.//Gotta say, between you and me, I'm more of a Nagalita fan myself.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>King Krakatoa</>, long may he reign, really showed his mettle at the last council meeting.//Sorted out a heated dispute over seaweed farming borders with just a few words. Drama, drama.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>King Krakatoa</>, long may he reign, really showed his mettle at the last council meeting.//Sorted out a heated dispute over seaweed farming borders with just a few words. Drama, drama.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>King Krakatoa</>, long may he reign, has this tradition – every year on his coronation day, he swims out to the furthest reef.//Says it's his way of staying connected to every part of his kingdom, from the shallow waters to the deep trenches. That's real humility for you.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>King Krakatoa</>, long may he reign, has this tradition – every year on his coronation day, he swims out to the furthest reef.//Says it's his way of staying connected to every part of his kingdom, from the shallow waters to the deep trenches. That's real humility for you.
